The paper discusses neural network models for algorithmic tasks, which are typically studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The focus on neural network architectures and loss terms suggests a connection to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category as well. The specific algorithmic tasks studied, including copy, parentheses parsing, and binary addition, are often studied in the natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) communities.
